  "body": "A function that can filter children would be very useful.  The most common case for this is implementing `<ShowMore max={5}>{items}</ShowMore>`.  \n\nLike map, forEach, etc. it traverses.  The index should be index at current depth, and the depth should be 1 for the first level, and increasing thereafter.\n\n``` jsx\n\nvar ShowMore = React.createClass({\n  render: function(){\n    var children, showMore = this.state.showMore;\n\n    if (showMore) {\n      children = this.props.children;\n    }\n    else {\n      children = React.Children.filter(this.props.children, this.limit);\n    }\n    return (\n      <div>\n        {children}\n      {!showMore && <button onClick={this.showMore}>Show More</button>}\n      </div>\n    );\n  },\n  showMore: function(){\n    this.setState({showMore: true});\n  },\n  limit: function(child, i, depth) {\n    return depth > 1 || i < this.props.limit;\n  },\n  getInitialState: function(){\n    return {showMore: false}\n  }\n});\n```\n",
